text: Kevin Moore (born 30 November 1965, in St Johns Lakemba, New South Wales, Australia) is a rugby league coach and former player. He was the head coach for the Bulldogs in the NRL from 2009 to 2011. As a player, he played as a scrum-half. ==References== == Other websites == *Bulldogs profile Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:Australian rugby league players Category:Rugby league players from Sydney Category:Rugby league coaches
